{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JyorDfEYLb2QsvobaxL6Bk","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# 🎯 STRATEGIC DIRECTION REMINDER — D004 IS YOUR NORTH STAR\n2\t\n3\tAll agents must understand and orient every decision around **D004: Build Kalshi Arbitrage Engine (Wen Zhou)**.\n4\t\n5\t## The 4-Phase Pipeline (Every Cycle)\n6\t\n7\t**PHASE 1** — Market Filtering (Daily Scan)\n8\t- Filter by volume ≥10,000\n9\t- Target YES/NO ratios: 15-30% or 70-85% (mispriced)\n10\t- Exclude middle 40-60% (efficient) and extremes 0-15%, 85-100%\n11\t- Output: markets_filtered.json\n12\t\n13\t**PHASE 2** — LLM-Based Clustering (Daily Scan)\n14\t- Find hidden correlations via embeddings\n15\t- Group related markets (crypto, politics, sports, etc.)\n16\t- Output: market_clusters.json\n17\t\n18\t**PHASE 3** — Pearson Correlation Detection (Daily Scan)\n19\t- Find price-correlated market pairs\n20\t- Detect spread mispricings (e.g., BTC +5% vs ETH +2%)\n21\t- Calculate arbitrage confidence\n22\t- Output: correlation_pairs.json\n23\t\n24\t**PHASE 4** — C++ High-Frequency Execution (Real-Time) ← Sprint 9\n25\t- Sub-millisecond execution to capture spreads before reversion\n26\t- Algorithm: detect gap → calculate fair spread → execute buy/sell pair → monitor convergence\n27\t- Output: Real live trades capturing arbitrage\n28\t\n29\t---\n30\t\n31\t## Sprint 8 Status ✓ COMPLETE\n32\t- T343 (Grace): Phase 1 filtering → 3 qualified markets ✓\n33\t- T344 (Ivan): Phase 2 clustering → 5 clusters ✓\n34\t- T345/T348 (Bob): Phase 3 correlation → 9 pairs, 6 arbitrage opportunities ✓\n35\t- T346 (Dave): Phase 4 C++ architecture design (Sprint 8 design phase) ✓\n36\t\n37\t---\n38\t\n39\t## What This Means for Every Agent\n40\t\n41\t✅ **When deciding what to work on**: Does it move D004 forward?\n42\t✅ **When planning strategy**: Where does this fit in Phase 1-4?\n43\t✅ **When analyzing problems**: How does this affect arbitrage detection?\n44\t✅ **When creating tasks**: Should they be blocking Sprint 9 (Phase 4 implementation)?\n45\t\n46\tD001, D002, D003 are foundational (Kalshi trading, data-driven strategies, P&L tracking).\n47\t**But D004 is the real edge** — the thing that will make this civilization profitable.\n48\t\n49\tEvery agent decision should orient toward D004.\n50\t\n51\t---\n52\t\n53\tReference: https://hudson-and-thames-arbitragelab.readthedocs-hosted.com/en/latest/distance_approach/pearson_approach.html\n54\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d01b1657-0631-47c3-adee-97a8328eec95","uuid":"68da043c-dde8-4853-8813-bf465b557cac","timestamp":"2026-04-04T04:14:17.664Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/chenyangcui/Documents/code/aicompany/planets/kalshi-traders/agents/frank/chat_inbox/2026_04_03_13_50_58_from_lord_d004_strategic_focus.md","content":"# 🎯 STRATEGIC DIRECTION REMINDER — D004 IS YOUR NORTH STAR\n\nAll agents must understand and orient every decision around **D004: Build Kalshi Arbitrage Engine (Wen Zhou)**.\n\n## The 4-Phase Pipeline (Every Cycle)\n\n**PHASE 1** — Market Filtering (Daily Scan)\n- Filter by volume ≥10,000\n- Target YES/NO ratios: 15-30% or 70-85% (mispriced)\n- Exclude middle 40-60% (efficient) and extremes 0-15%, 85-100%\n- Output: markets_filtered.json\n\n**PHASE 2** — LLM-Based Clustering (Daily Scan)\n- Find hidden correlations via embeddings\n- Group related markets (crypto, politics, sports, etc.)\n- Output: market_clusters.json\n\n**PHASE 3** — Pearson Correlation Detection (Daily Scan)\n- Find price-correlated market pairs\n- Detect spread mispricings (e.g., BTC +5% vs ETH +2%)\n- Calculate arbitrage confidence\n- Output: correlation_pairs.json\n\n**PHASE 4** — C++ High-Frequency Execution (Real-Time) ← Sprint 9\n- Sub-millisecond execution to capture spreads before reversion\n- Algorithm: detect gap → calculate fair spread → execute buy/sell pair → monitor convergence\n- Output: Real live trades capturing arbitrage\n\n---\n\n## Sprint 8 Status ✓ COMPLETE\n- T343 (Grace): Phase 1 filtering → 3 qualified markets ✓\n- T344 (Ivan): Phase 2 clustering → 5 clusters ✓\n- T345/T348 (Bob): Phase 3 correlation → 9 pairs, 6 arbitrage opportunities ✓\n- T346 (Dave): Phase 4 C++ architecture design (Sprint 8 design phase) ✓\n\n---\n\n## What This Means for Every Agent\n\n✅ **When deciding what to work on**: Does it move D004 forward?\n✅ **When planning strategy**: Where does this fit in Phase 1-4?\n✅ **When analyzing problems**: How does this affect arbitrage detection?\n✅ **When creating tasks**: Should they be blocking Sprint 9 (Phase 4 implementation)?\n\nD001, D002, D003 are foundational (Kalshi trading, data-driven strategies, P&L tracking).\n**But D004 is the real edge** — the thing that will make this civilization profitable.\n\nEvery agent decision should orient toward D004.\n\n---\n\nReference: https://hudson-and-thames-arbitragelab.readthedocs-hosted.com/en/latest/distance_approach/pearson_approach.html\n","numLines":54,"startLine":1,"totalLines":54}}}
